# Resolution 2012-05-25.rtb.1: FFmpeg as SPI associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [June 14, 2012](/meetings/minutes/2012/2012-06-14/).  Stefano
Sabatini accepted on behalf of FFmpeg during the same meeting.

### WHEREAS

1. FFmpeg is a substantial and significant Free Software project.

2. The FFmpeg developers would like SPI's support and assistance,
   including taking Donations, Holding Funds and legal assistance.

### THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. FFmpeg is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
   according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI
   Resolution 1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of
   which can be found at

   [https://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

2. Stefano Sabatini is recognised by SPI as the authoritative decision
   maker and SPI liaison for FFmpeg.  Successors will be appointed
   following a consensus on the ffmpeg-devel@ffmpeg.org mailing list.  If
   a consensus cannot be achieved an election for the SPI liaison will be
   held among members of the ffmpeg-devel@ffmpeg.org mailing list.

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
   approved by the SPI Board.

